Because to them, it's not a church.

1054
01:01:17,960 --> 01:01:20,280
It's a building on the corner
next to a liquor store.

1055
01:01:20,480 --> 01:01:24,520
Where the neon wine-and-beer sign
is brighter than the cross.

1056
01:01:24,680 --> 01:01:28,000
You know, if we separate the two
like I've been wanting...

1057
01:01:28,200 --> 01:01:30,120
...maybe ours would shine brighter.

1058
01:01:30,320 --> 01:01:32,040
Brighter because we're brighter,
Deacon?

1059
01:01:32,240 --> 01:01:34,240
Or brighter
because we're separate?

1060
01:01:37,240 --> 01:01:39,520
I want the key to that cabinet
right there...

1061
01:01:39,720 --> 01:01:42,440
...and I know you got it, so don't lie.

1062
01:01:50,080 --> 01:01:52,480
Were y'all trying
to blow open the safe?

1063
01:01:54,680 --> 01:01:55,800
It wasn't my idea.

1064
01:02:23,800 --> 01:02:25,240
You find it?

1065
01:02:25,720 --> 01:02:28,320
Do it look like I found it? Let's go.

1066
01:02:28,520 --> 01:02:31,040
What kind of name is LeeJohn,
anyway?

1067
01:02:35,720 --> 01:02:38,920
When I was born, my mother had
two boyfriends. Lee and John.

1068
01:02:39,520 --> 01:02:43,000
She ain't know who my real father
was, so she named me LeeJohn.

1069
01:02:43,920 --> 01:02:44,840
Of course.

1070
01:02:49,840 --> 01:02:51,560
I don't think I would've told that.

1071
01:02:54,960 --> 01:02:56,440
Hot.

1072
01:03:01,440 --> 01:03:03,000
You know...

1073
01:03:03,440 --> 01:03:05,960
...if that doesn't work,
there's always Sho-Blo.

1074
01:03:06,160 --> 01:03:08,360
Yeah, well, maybe it'll work
if I can get...

1075
01:03:09,400 --> 01:03:11,560
If I can get the light pointed straight.

1076
01:03:11,760 --> 01:03:15,120
Oh, yeah, the problem is the light.
It's my fault.

1077
01:03:16,840 --> 01:03:18,360
I'm hungry.

1078
01:03:18,960 --> 01:03:20,920
I'm hungry too.

1079
01:03:22,040 --> 01:03:23,200
When are you not hungry?

1080
01:03:23,400 --> 01:03:26,600
Well, I have some leftover chicken,
ham, potato salad, greens...

1081
01:03:26,800 --> 01:03:30,240
...and some peach cobbler
from this afternoon's dinner.

1082
01:03:30,440 --> 01:03:33,600
I could fix something up
if y'all would like to eat.

1083
01:03:36,200 --> 01:03:39,840
What about a 8-year-old boy who was
hungry and didn't know how to swim?

1084
01:03:40,040 --> 01:03:43,160
Was scared to get baptized because
he thought he was gonna drown?

1085
01:03:43,360 --> 01:03:45,640
<i>- How come he couldn't eat, huh?
- What?</i>

1086
01:03:51,200 --> 01:03:54,680
Is that a yes or a no on the chicken?

1087
01:03:59,440 --> 01:04:02,120
How do you know how to fix
air conditioners, anyway?

1088
01:04:03,120 --> 01:04:06,600
When you grow up in a house
and everything around you is broke...

1089
01:04:06,800 --> 01:04:08,320
...that's what you do.

1090
01:04:09,040 --> 01:04:11,440
You fix things. Watch this.

1091
01:04:14,280 --> 01:04:15,640
Oh, my gosh.

1092
01:04:15,840 --> 01:04:17,720
Hit that light.

1093
01:04:17,920 --> 01:04:20,040
Don't wanna electrocute myself.

1094
01:04:20,200 --> 01:04:23,240
Wow, you know, this thing has never
worked right. You're pretty good.

1095
01:04:23,440 --> 01:04:26,480
I mean, you're obviously not good,
but what you just did was good.

1096
01:04:26,680 --> 01:04:29,800
- You always so stank?
- Only when I'm hungry.

1097
01:04:29,960 --> 01:04:33,680
And when I'm being held hostage at
gunpoint, I get a little a cranky.

1098
01:04:33,880 --> 01:04:36,040
Maybe I got a good reason.
You ever think of that?

1099
01:04:36,240 --> 01:04:39,400
You mean like Robin Hood?
Or, in your case, robbing the hood?

1100
01:04:39,560 --> 01:04:41,800
Take from the poor
and give to the poor?

1101
01:04:42,000 --> 01:04:43,800
Trying to give something
I never had.

1102
01:04:44,000 --> 01:04:46,120
- A felony record?
- No, a father.

1103
01:04:46,320 --> 01:04:48,040
Do you have a tissue I can borrow?

1104
01:04:48,200 --> 01:04:50,120
I seem to have left mine
in the bucket...

1105
01:04:50,280 --> 01:04:54,240
...along with anything that would
beep, buzz or get on your nerves.

1106
01:04:54,440 --> 01:04:57,760
My mother died when I was 6.
You don't see me robbing a church.

1107
01:04:57,960 --> 01:05:01,120
Yeah, sometimes you gotta do what
you gotta do to get where you going.

1108
01:05:01,320 --> 01:05:02,600
Would that be jail?

1109
01:05:02,760 --> 01:05:05,640
Parenting from within the penal
system, that would be brilliant.

1110
01:05:05,840 --> 01:05:07,440
That's not smart.

1111
01:05:07,640 --> 01:05:10,400
- You wouldn't even understand.
- And I don't want to.

1112
01:05:10,600 --> 01:05:12,480
What you care for anyway,
church girl?

1113
01:05:12,680 --> 01:05:14,200
- I don't.
- Good. Neither do I.

1114
01:05:14,400 --> 01:05:15,720
- Good.
- Good.

1115
01:05:15,920 --> 01:05:16,880
Good.

1116
01:05:17,080 --> 01:05:18,200
G- double-O-D.

1117
01:05:18,400 --> 01:05:19,600
- Good.
- Perfect.

1118
01:05:19,800 --> 01:05:20,800
Wait a minute.

1119
01:05:26,920 --> 01:05:28,960
- Thank you.
- Oh, Sister Doris' chicken.

1120
01:05:29,160 --> 01:05:30,720
That's good.

1121
01:05:40,520 --> 01:05:43,680
I brought you some food.
I know you hungry too.

1122
01:05:44,040 --> 01:05:46,800
I don't have to get baptized, right?
Because I can't swim.

1123
01:05:47,000 --> 01:05:48,720
No.

1124
01:05:50,120 --> 01:05:51,840
- There you are.
- Thank you.

1125
01:05:52,680 --> 01:05:54,200
It's good, ain't it?

1126
01:05:54,400 --> 01:05:57,120
Something about you
remind me of my husband.

1127
01:05:57,480 --> 01:06:01,680
I think it's your nose.
He had a wide one just like you.

1128
01:06:01,880 --> 01:06:06,040
Oh, he was a beautiful man
inside and out.

1129
01:06:06,400 --> 01:06:10,200
One of the best deacons this church
ever had. No matter what they say.

1130
01:06:10,680 --> 01:06:13,120
He loved my cooking too.

1131
01:06:13,320 --> 01:06:17,800
You know, today was his birthday,
and nobody remembered but me.

1132
01:06:18,000 --> 01:06:20,360
He's been gone, what, six years?

1133
01:06:20,560 --> 01:06:24,000
He loved the birthday parties
I planned for him.

1134
01:06:24,200 --> 01:06:27,200
You like birthday parties, Leonard?
I mean, LeeJohn?

1135
01:06:27,400 --> 01:06:30,600
- I don't know, I never had one.
- You never had a birthday party?

1136
01:06:30,760 --> 01:06:35,040
When they took me to my foster home,
they lost my birth certificate...

1137
01:06:35,240 --> 01:06:37,960
...so nobody never knew
when my birthday was.

1138
01:06:39,960 --> 01:06:41,240
I know when it is.

1139
01:06:41,440 --> 01:06:44,040
You do? When?

1140
01:06:44,240 --> 01:06:45,760
Today.

1141
01:06:49,200 --> 01:06:50,440
Give me your hand.

1142
01:07:33,920 --> 01:07:36,000
Happy birthday.

1143
01:07:36,800 --> 01:07:38,440
Come on, now.

1144
01:07:39,320 --> 01:07:40,440
It's all right.

1145
01:07:42,520 --> 01:07:43,800
It's all right.

1146
01:07:45,000 --> 01:07:46,080
Yes, it is.

1147
01:07:49,640 --> 01:07:51,400
It's all right.

1148
01:07:52,840 --> 01:07:53,800
LeeJohn.

1149
01:07:55,720 --> 01:07:56,800
The hell you doing?

1150
01:07:57,800 --> 01:07:59,080
You hungry?

1151
01:08:00,280 --> 01:08:02,840
It's blowing harder
than it's ever blown before.

1152
01:08:03,040 --> 01:08:04,760
It's a miracle.

1153
01:08:04,960 --> 01:08:09,040
It's air. The same air as before,
just a little cooler.

1154
01:08:09,240 --> 01:08:11,320
A young man
as good with his hands as you are...

1155
01:08:11,520 --> 01:08:13,280
...should have more options
than robbing.

1156
01:08:13,480 --> 01:08:15,680
- I'm all out of options now.
- That's not true, son.

1157
01:08:15,880 --> 01:08:17,240
Don't, that's not true.

1158
01:08:17,440 --> 01:08:20,040
You're only out of options
when you stop looking for them.

1159
01:08:22,920 --> 01:08:24,640
- Durell?
- Go back over there.

1160
01:08:24,840 --> 01:08:27,840
- I need to talk to you.
- I don't wanna talk to you right now.

1161
01:08:28,040 --> 01:08:29,920
Can I talk to you for one minute?

1162
01:08:30,120 --> 01:08:33,760
I don't wanna do this anymore.
These people ain't did nothing to us.

1163
01:08:33,960 --> 01:08:36,520
You came and got me from
my grandmama house with this...

1164
01:08:36,720 --> 01:08:39,480
...and you don't wanna go through
with it? Trying to punk out?

1165
01:08:39,680 --> 01:08:40,840
I ain't no punk, man.

1166
01:08:41,040 --> 01:08:43,080
You ain't forgot
you need this as bad as me?

1167
01:08:43,280 --> 01:08:45,960
I'll think of something,
and I don't know what it is.

1168
01:08:46,160 --> 01:08:48,120
But I know...

1169
01:08:48,880 --> 01:08:51,040
...it ain't gonna be this.

1170
01:08:51,240 --> 01:08:52,680
Durell, not this.

1171
01:09:08,800 --> 01:09:11,680
Our jobs would be easier if people
would just listen and go home.

1172
01:09:11,880 --> 01:09:13,760
Pastor knows they
supposed to be out by 10.

1173
01:09:13,960 --> 01:09:16,280
I don't know what y'all did,
but I don't like it.

1174
01:09:17,000 --> 01:09:20,800
Now stop playing with me and just
give me the money and we can leave.

1175
01:09:21,000 --> 01:09:23,360
For some reason,
y'all think I won't use these.

1176
01:09:23,560 --> 01:09:25,880
It's simple! Just give up the money!

1177
01:09:26,560 --> 01:09:28,480
I thought you were supposed
to be cleaning.

1178
01:09:28,680 --> 01:09:29,800
I told you, he's blind.

1179
01:09:29,960 --> 01:09:31,880
- Can't see, and he's deaf.
- He can't hear.

1180
01:09:32,080 --> 01:09:35,200
I've been cleaning this church
for 30 years. Seen a lot of things...

1181
01:09:35,400 --> 01:09:36,680
...found a lot of things too.

1182
01:09:36,880 --> 01:09:38,560
Why y'all got this man cleaning?

1183
01:09:38,760 --> 01:09:41,080
- Because he's free.
- But never nothing like this.

1184
01:09:43,920 --> 01:09:45,280
Evening.

1185
01:09:46,960 --> 01:09:49,840
All right, get back! Sit back!
Sit down.

1186
01:09:52,280 --> 01:09:54,840
- Look at all that money.
- Yeah.

1187
01:09:55,040 --> 01:09:57,920
It's probably just the cleaning man,
you know?

1188
01:10:01,160 --> 01:10:02,240
Or not.

1189
01:10:05,640 --> 01:10:09,200
We got a 10-31 in progress at the
corner of Preston and Greenmount.

1190
01:10:09,400 --> 01:10:11,640
A perp with a gun.
Request for immediate backup.

1191
01:10:11,840 --> 01:10:13,120
That's our money.

1192
01:10:13,320 --> 01:10:14,560
Son, that's God's money.

1193
01:10:18,760 --> 01:10:20,680
LeeJohn, let's roll.

1194
01:10:22,520 --> 01:10:24,240
LeeJohn.

1195
01:10:26,320 --> 01:10:28,480
I think I'm gonna stay here
with them, Durell.

1196
01:10:35,960 --> 01:10:38,200
It's your son, isn't it?

1197
01:10:39,600 --> 01:10:41,080
Tell him what you're doing.

1198
01:10:44,680 --> 01:10:49,120
You want him to hear it on the news?
Or read about it in tomorrow's paper?

1199
01:11:02,920 --> 01:11:08,120
I get up every morning, and I take
my son to school every morning.

1200
01:11:09,480 --> 01:11:12,440
He look at me, he don't see no thug.

1201
