This is a travesty!

1439
01:25:14,280 --> 01:25:16,440
Praise the Lord.

1440
01:25:17,320 --> 01:25:18,720
Pastor! Pastor!

1441
01:25:23,520 --> 01:25:25,720
Oh, yeah!

1442
01:25:33,320 --> 01:25:34,920
I'm just trying to get...

1443
01:25:35,880 --> 01:25:38,880
Ten chairs, $ 1200 apiece.

1444
01:25:39,080 --> 01:25:41,120
Check it out.
You stole them wheelchairs...

1445
01:25:41,320 --> 01:25:43,080
...and then somebody stole them
from us.

1446
01:25:43,280 --> 01:25:45,320
So the way I look at that,
I think we even.

1447
01:25:45,520 --> 01:25:49,440
My baby mama might have
took my son away from me today.

1448
01:25:49,640 --> 01:25:52,480
And if y'all gonna kill us
over some chairs, then go ahead.

1449
01:25:54,280 --> 01:25:57,720
But kill him first
because it was his dumb-ass idea.

1450
01:25:57,920 --> 01:25:59,800
We still have business.

1451
01:26:00,480 --> 01:26:02,400
Go get your son, man.

1452
01:26:06,360 --> 01:26:10,400
- Ticktock, gunshot.
- Leave me.

1453
01:26:12,080 --> 01:26:13,800
Omunique?

1454
01:26:16,160 --> 01:26:17,400
Omunique?

1455
01:26:22,440 --> 01:26:25,440
Where did you get it, huh? Where?

1456
01:26:25,680 --> 01:26:27,880
What is this?
I don't know what this is.

1457
01:26:28,040 --> 01:26:30,960
Rell and I were leaving for the train
station when I hear a knock.

1458
01:26:31,160 --> 01:26:33,880
I open it, nobody's there,
just this bag...

1459
01:26:34,080 --> 01:26:38,440
...filled with $ 17,342 exactly!

1460
01:26:38,640 --> 01:26:41,480
You stole it, didn't you?
Did you steal this?

1461
01:26:41,640 --> 01:26:44,040
I know where it came from,
but I did not steal it!

1462
01:26:44,240 --> 01:26:46,520
If I told you,
you wouldn't even believe me.

1463
01:26:46,720 --> 01:26:48,680
I wouldn't even believe me.

1464
01:26:48,880 --> 01:26:53,000
Look. Now, somebody gave me
this money.

1465
01:26:54,160 --> 01:26:58,280
But since we got it,
I need to know something.

1466
01:26:58,480 --> 01:27:00,960
You staying or you going?

1467
01:27:01,160 --> 01:27:02,920
- That's not fair.
- You got enough money.

1468
01:27:03,080 --> 01:27:05,680
You got what you need.
What you gonna do?

1469
01:27:06,000 --> 01:27:08,040
You gonna take my son
away from me?

1470
01:27:09,000 --> 01:27:10,280
And move to Atlanta?

1471
01:27:12,040 --> 01:27:15,720
Don't take my son from me. Okay?
That's all I got.

1472
01:27:16,640 --> 01:27:21,000
All right, you wanna break me now?
He's all I got. I ain't got nothing else.

1473
01:27:21,640 --> 01:27:24,000
I'll do whatever I can.
I'll come around more.

1474
01:27:24,200 --> 01:27:26,920
Whatever you need from me,
I can do that.

1475
01:27:27,080 --> 01:27:29,640
- I'm a different man now.
- What's different?

1476
01:27:29,840 --> 01:27:33,760
I'm different. I'm changed.

1477
01:27:39,240 --> 01:27:41,000
You gonna stay?

1478
01:27:43,880 --> 01:27:45,840
What you gonna do?

1479
01:27:56,880 --> 01:27:58,200
We're...

1480
01:27:59,760 --> 01:28:01,640
We're gonna stay.

1481
01:28:06,600 --> 01:28:08,480
Thank you.

1482
01:28:16,320 --> 01:28:18,920
I told you. Didn't I tell you?
Didn't I tell you?

1483
01:28:19,080 --> 01:28:21,800
- Yes.
- Ain't nobody gonna take you from me.

1484
01:28:23,080 --> 01:28:24,600
Nobody.

1485
01:28:26,400 --> 01:28:28,240
I love you.

1486
01:28:38,400 --> 01:28:39,880
Thank you.

1487
01:28:43,240 --> 01:28:48,160
<i>It was no mistake how those two boys
landed in our church.</i>

1488
01:28:48,360 --> 01:28:54,560
<i>They weren't all bad,
just 180 degrees from good.</i>

1489
01:28:54,760 --> 01:28:58,560
<i>They just needed a change
in direction...</i>

1490
01:28:58,760 --> 01:29:01,600
<i>...and that's what we all need
sometimes.</i>

1491
01:29:27,880 --> 01:29:28,840
<i>I figure...</i>

1492
01:29:29,040 --> 01:29:33,720
<i>...if God can give these two boys
a second chance...</i>

1493
01:29:35,720 --> 01:29:37,000
<i>...then why can't we?</i>

1494
01:29:38,280 --> 01:29:40,320
<i>Why can't we?</i>

